# Environment Configuration for iFi Backend

# Server Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
API_VERSION=v1

# Plaid Configuration (Sandbox - for development)
PLAID_CLIENT_ID=your_sandbox_client_id_here
PLAID_SECRET=your_sandbox_secret_here
PLAID_ENV=sandbox
PLAID_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_verification_secret

# Production Plaid Configuration (uncomment for production)
# PLAID_CLIENT_ID=your_production_client_id_here
# PLAID_SECRET=your_production_secret_here
# PLAID_ENV=production

# Database Configuration (PostgreSQL)
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=ifi_db
DB_USER=ifi_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_db_password_here

# Security Configuration
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
ENCRYPTION_KEY=your_32_byte_encryption_key_here_64_chars
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_here

# CORS Configuration
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000

# Rate Limiting
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=900000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

# Webhook Configuration
WEBHOOK_URL=http://localhost:3000/api/plaid/webhook

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=info
LOG_FILE=logs/app.log

# Session Configuration
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret_here

# Email Configuration (for notifications)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your_email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your_app_password

# Frontend URL
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# SSL Configuration (production)
SSL_KEY_PATH=/path/to/ssl/key.pem
SSL_CERT_PATH=/path/to/ssl/cert.pem


comment: Breakdown of sections:
Server Configuration

NODE_ENV: Mode the server runs in (e.g., development or production).

PORT: Which port the server listens on (3000 here).

API_VERSION: Version of your backend API.

Plaid Configuration

PLAID_CLIENT_ID and PLAID_SECRET: Your Plaid credentials for authentication (sandbox = test environment).

PLAID_ENV: Which Plaid environment to use (sandbox for testing, production for real).

PLAID_WEBHOOK_SECRET: Secret to verify Plaid webhook messages.

The production keys are commented out, ready to be used when deploying live.

Database Configuration

Info for connecting to your PostgreSQL database: host, port, database name, username, and password.

Security Configuration

ENCRYPTION_KEY: A secret key used to encrypt sensitive data.

JWT_SECRET: Secret key for signing JSON Web Tokens (used for user authentication).

Both keys should be randomly generated and kept private.

CORS Configuration

ALLOWED_ORIGINS: List of URLs allowed to communicate with your backend (to prevent unauthorized cross-site requests).

Rate Limiting

Controls how many requests a user can make in a time window to prevent abuse.

RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS: Length of time window in milliseconds (here, 15 minutes).

RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS: Max requests allowed in that window (100 here).

Webhook Configuration

WEBHOOK_URL: The URL where your backend listens for Plaid webhook notifications.

Logging

LOG_LEVEL: How much detail to log (info means general info).

LOG_FILE: Where to save log files.

Session Configuration

SESSION_SECRET: Secret key used to sign and secure user sessions.

Email Configuration

Settings to send emails (e.g., notifications), like SMTP server, port, username, and password.

Frontend URL

URL where your frontend app is running (used in some responses or redirects).

SSL Configuration (for production)

Paths to SSL certificate and key files to enable HTTPS on your server.